				<node id="TranslatedStringKey">
					<attribute id="Content" type="28" handle="h34fa90bdg6d1fg4ee8gb3e7g8c3694c70fae" value="Aerotheurge spells trigger a Vaporize effect wherever they hit. If a Geomancy spell is targeted within a cloud, all enemies within receive 1 turn of Suffocating, up to 2 turns. If an enemy already has 2 turns or more of Suffocating, it increases its effectiveness by 20% instead, up to 200%.&lt;br&gt;Apply Wet or Chilled on a Burning target or vice-versa will trigger Thermal Shock. When it is active, surface ticks of normal Steam Clouds deal Water damage. Fire and Water damage received while Thermal Shock will use the lowest of both corresponding resistances and benefit of a bonus of 25 ArPen."/>
